h merely to insert water basins and fountains at the appropriate spots in architectural drawings. As early as the design stage the planner must begin to think about where the water is going to come from, where it is going to drain, and how it is going to be cleaned.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aArchitecture. 4aDesign. 4aGarden. 4aLandscape Architecture. 4aPark. 4aPlace. 4aStudent handbook. 4aTextbook architecture. 4aTextbook landscape architecture. 4aTextbook professional practice. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh1 aBott, Cornelia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISHz978303561170008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z97831102385700 cEPUBz97830356129810 cprintz978376438662740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303561287540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035612875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035612875/original  a978-3-0356-1170-0  BASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISH  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062112-9  DGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GAAc2000d2014